What does this program print if the input is `42\nHello World\n`?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
int main() {
    int n;
    std::cin >> n;
    std::string line;
    std::getline(std::cin, line);
    std::cout << n << "|" << line << "\n";
}
```

